      <hedline>
        <hl1>Summertime Dues</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mary Hafeli letter scores teen Walter Kirn, in July 9 Way We Live Now essay, for not quitting summer job that called for him to cheat and steal3</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Walter Kirn wonders what sort of character teenagers are supposed to develop from working at summer jobs. To start, how about the sense to leave jobs that call for cheating and stealing? Entering the working world forces kids to make ethical judgments in situations such as Kirn describes. This is a bad thing?</p>
        <p>Mary Hafeli  Cold Spring, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
